Rule-based bot

+---------------------------+     +---------------------------+     +----------------------+
| Exact command             | --> | If/else matcher           | --> | Runs action          |
| "/restart pod-x"          |     | fixed keyword rules       |     | kubectl restart      |
+---------------------------+     +---------------------------+     +----------------------+

No match → fails or "command not recognized"


LLM-powered bot

+---------------------------+     +---------------------------+     +----------------------+
| Natural language          | --> | LLM reasoning             | --> | Action executor      |
| "checkout keeps crashing" |     | checks logs, picks action |     | human-approved       |
+---------------------------+     +---------------------------+     +----------------------+

Handles phrasing it's never seen, decides the action itself

Top row is the old-style bot — it only fires when input matches a predefined pattern, and fails outside that. Bottom row is an 
LLM-powered bot — it interprets open-ended phrasing, reasons over your logs/metrics, and decides the action itself, ideally still with 
a human-approval gate before anything destructive runs.

